Text is defined as a Data-type
Text is converted to other data-types
- 1-dimensional data: textual documents, program source code, alphabetical lists, etc.
- 2-dimensional data: geographic maps, floorplants, newspaper layouts, 2-axes dia-grams, etc.
- Temporal data: all kinds of timelines.
- Multi-dimensional data: relational and statistical databases.
- Tree data: genealogical data, file systems trees, genetic data, etc.
- Network data: social relationships, computer networks, etc.
